	(111, 105, 'Internet of things', 'The internet of things, or IoT, is a system of interrelated computing devices, mechanical and digital machines, objects, animals or people that are provided with unique identifiers (UIDs) and the bility to transfer data over a network without requiring human-to-human or human-to-computer interaction.', 161, 161);

